{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"what-are-issue-labels\"><a href=\"#what-are-issue-labels\" aria-label=\"what are issue labels permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What are issue labels?</h2>\n<p>Issue labels are a tool in GitHub that are used to group issues into one or more categories.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/issues/labels\">Check out Gatsby’s labels (and their descriptions)</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"why-label-issues\"><a href=\"#why-label-issues\" aria-label=\"why label issues permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Why label issues?</h2>\n<p>Gatsby is a very active project with many new issues opened each day. Labelling issues helps by identifying:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>good issues for new contributors to work on</li>\n<li>reported and confirmed bugs</li>\n<li>feature requests</li>\n<li>duplicate issues</li>\n<li>issues that are stalled or blocked</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"who-can-label-issues\"><a href=\"#who-can-label-issues\" aria-label=\"who can label issues permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Who can label issues?</h2>\n<p>Anyone who’s a member of the <a href=\"https://github.com/orgs/gatsbyjs/teams/maintainers\">Gatsby Maintainers team</a> can label issues.</p>\n<p>You can get an invite to the team by having a Pull Request merged into the Gatsby project. Check out the list of <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/labels/%F0%9F%93%8D%20status%3A%20help%20wanted\"><code class=\"language-text\">help wanted</code></a> issues and the <a href=\"/docs/how-to-contribute/\">How To Contribute Guide</a> to get started.</p>\n<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> If you’ve already had a pull request merged and you have <em>not</em> been invited to the maintainers team, please go to <a href=\"https://store.gatsbyjs.org/\">the dashboard</a> and request a discount code. You should get an invite to the team — <em>and you get free Gatsby swag!</em> If that doesn’t work, please email team@gatsbyjs.com and we’ll get you invited.</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-label-an-issue\"><a href=\"#how-to-label-an-issue\" aria-label=\"how to label an issue permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to label an issue</h2>\n<p>Ideally, every issue should have a single <code class=\"language-text\">type:</code> label applied to it. Optionally a <code class=\"language-text\">status:</code> label or other labels may also be applied.</p>\n<p>Before continuing, get familiar with <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/issues/labels\">Gatsby’s issue labels and their descriptions</a>.</p>\n<p>The broad steps to labelling an issue are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Read an issue</li>\n<li>Choose the labels that apply to that issue</li>\n<li>That’s it - sit back and relax, maybe take a few moments to enjoy the satisfaction of a job well done</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The rest of this document will describe how to choose the right labels for an issue.</p>\n<h3 id=\"find-an-issue-that-youre-interested-in\"><a href=\"#find-an-issue-that-youre-interested-in\" aria-label=\"find an issue that youre interested in permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Find an issue that you’re interested in</h3>\n<p>Start with <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/issues\">Gatsby’s issues list</a> and scroll through until you see a recent one that strikes your interest. Alternatively, you can view the <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+no%3Alabel\">list of unlabelled issues</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"read-the-issue\"><a href=\"#read-the-issue\" aria-label=\"read the issue permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Read the issue</h3>\n<p>Read the issue and any comments to understand what the issue is about.</p>\n<h3 id=\"choose-one-type-label\"><a href=\"#choose-one-type-label\" aria-label=\"choose one type label permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Choose one <code class=\"language-text\">type:</code> label</h3>\n<p>Choose a type label from the <em>labels</em> dropdown to the right-hand side of the issue.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/46098fb0bfd210ed7bca82ff2ea940e4/e9eb8/github-label-list.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 331px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 171.90332326283988%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #ffffff;\"\n        alt=\"GitHub label dropdown\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/46098fb0bfd210ed7bca82ff2ea940e4/e9eb8/github-label-list.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/46098fb0bfd210ed7bca82ff2ea940e4/bf0a6/github-label-list.png 197w,\n/static/46098fb0bfd210ed7bca82ff2ea940e4/e9eb8/github-label-list.png 331w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 331px) 100vw, 331px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>You can check through the <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/issues/labels\">label descriptions</a> for more information on each one.</p>\n<p>The most common type of issue is <code class=\"language-text\">type: question or discussion</code>, typically you can apply this to issues that are open-ended or have no clear next step.</p>\n<p>It’s OK to change the type of an issue as more information becomes available. What starts as <code class=\"language-text\">type: question or discussion</code>, might later need to be changed to <code class=\"language-text\">type: bug</code>.</p>\n<p>Changing labels is quick and easily reversible, so don’t worry too much about applying a “wrong” label.</p>\n<p>Choose an appropriate <code class=\"language-text\">type:</code> label and you’re ready to move on to the next step.</p>\n<h3 id=\"choose-a-status-label-optional\"><a href=\"#choose-a-status-label-optional\" aria-label=\"choose a status label optional permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Choose a <code class=\"language-text\">status:</code> label (optional)</h3>\n<p>Check through the <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/issues/labels\"><code class=\"language-text\">status:</code> labels (and their descriptions)</a>, if any apply to this issue add them as necessary.</p>\n<p>Examples of applying <code class=\"language-text\">status:</code> labels might be:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>An issue that depends on an external dependency being changed could be labelled with <code class=\"language-text\">status: blocked</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>An issue with a clear description of how it can be resolved could be labelled <code class=\"language-text\">status: help wanted</code>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>An issue that’s missing information required to help the author could be labelled with <code class=\"language-text\">status: needs more info</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>An issue describing a bug without clear steps to reproduce could be labelled with <code class=\"language-text\">status: needs reproduction</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>An issue describing a bug where there are steps to reproduce the bug <em>and</em> you’ve run the code locally and seen the error yourself can be labelled <code class=\"language-text\">status: confirmed</code></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"choose-any-other-labels\"><a href=\"#choose-any-other-labels\" aria-label=\"choose any other labels permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Choose any other labels</h3>\n<p>There are a few other labels that can sometimes be applied to an issue. Here are some more examples of when to use them:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">good first issue</code> can be used when an issue is a small, clearly defined piece of work that could be completed by someone without in-depth knowledge of Gatsby and how it works. These issues are particularly suitable for people making their first open source contributions.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">stale?</code> can be used on an issue where the author has not replied to requests for further information in at least 20 days.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"finish\"><a href=\"#finish\" aria-label=\"finish permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Finish</h3>\n<p>And you’re done! You can call it a day or go back to the first step to label another issue.</p>\n<h2 id=\"conclusion\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>Labelling issues is a great way to help out on the Gatsby project regardless of your experience level.</p>","excerpt":"What are issue labels? Issue labels are a tool in GitHub that are used to group issues into one or more categories. Check out Gatsby’s…","timeToRead":4,"fields":{"slug":"/docs/how-to-label-an-issue/","anchor":"how-to-label-an-issue"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How to label an issue","overview":null,"issue":null},"parent":{"__typename":"File","relativePath":"docs/how-to-label-an-issue.md"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/docs/how-to-label-an-issue/"}}